wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Robson (3 May 1892 – 1960) was an English professional footballer who made 165 appearances in the Football League playing as a full back for Swansea Town, Durham City and Hartlepools United. He also played in the Southern League for Southend United and for Swansea Town before their election to the Football League. Robson was among the 35 men who enlisted for the Football Battalion at its formation.
